name: Sampath Kumar Balivada
bio: Sai Sampath Kumar Balivada is a seasoned Software Engineer at PayPal, based in Visakhapatnam, India. With a passion for crafting intuitive and engaging experiences, he specializes in ensuring transactional compliance across PayPal and its partners. Previously, he contributed significantly to Amazon Web Services (AWS), excelling in roles such as Cloud Support Associate. Sai Sampath holds a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science and Engineering and boasts certifications in AWS, Google Go programming, and open-source software development. As an organizer for GDG Vizag, he combines technical prowess with a commitment to community engagement, reflecting his dedication to both professional excellence and knowledge sharing.

name: Sasi Teja Kamsu
bio: Meet Sasi, an Engineer at Confluent, the visionary creators of Kafka. With a rich professional journey that includes roles at AWS and Cisco, Sasi is a seasoned expert in Kafka, Cloud technologies, and DevOps. He excels in designing and implementing real-time data streaming applications. A certified AWS Solutions Architect Associate, Sasi's passion for data science and machine learning is evident through a research paper in time series analytics. A dedicated community enthusiast, he's been an integral part of the GDG (Google Developer Groups) community since 2018
